notesStmt.note: The last quire is imperfect, with a lacuna after folio 140 and 148.
The 15th quire is now imperfect, with a lacuna after folio 194 and 202.
Folios 208r-209v: two appended folios, mutilated, written in two different Sefardi hands, of apparently 11 to 12th century, containing fragments of Talmud (Mo῾ed Katan and Eruvin).
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: Two fragments of Judeo-Arabic commentary of Yefet ben 'Eli on Exodus.

supportDesc.extent: [ii]+207+[ii] Part I: Folios 1-148. Part II: Folios 149-207.;

layoutDesc.layout: Part I: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 21; written lines: 21; The unpointed biblical text is embodied, followed by an Arabic translation. Catchword on every verso. Part II: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 21; written lines: 21; Hebrew text is embodied. Catchword on every verso.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Part I: Semi-cursive script of 15-16th century.Part II: Semi-cursive script of 16th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'Yefet. Commentary on Exodus. Arabic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2468.'
